# Build muninn daemon process with local IPC and adapter auto-start

## Parent Initiative

[[hook-mcp-integration-layer-for-claude-code]] (PROJEC-I-0011)

## Objective

Make `muninn` a long-running daemon process that owns the `MuninnEngine` impl and the memory/graph stores. Define a local-IPC contract (Unix socket on Linux/macOS; named pipe on Windows) so adapters — proxy, MCP server, hook scripts — can call engine methods without each spawning their own engine instance. Adapters auto-spawn the daemon when no socket is found.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `muninn daemon` subcommand starts the daemon. `muninn daemon stop`, `muninn daemon status` round it out.
- [ ] Socket path is repo-scoped: e.g. `$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/muninn/<repo-hash>.sock` (or platform equivalent). Document the discovery rule.
- [ ] Wire format: length-prefixed JSON, one request → one response. Each request carries a method name matching a `MuninnEngine` method plus its argument struct.
- [ ] Daemon is single-writer to SQLite — no other process opens the DB while it's running.
- [ ] `muninn daemon ensure` helper that no-ops if the daemon is up and spawns it otherwise. Idempotent under concurrent invocation (file-lock or socket-bind race handling).
- [ ] Adapters (proxy entry point, MCP, hook CLI) call `daemon ensure` on startup before issuing engine calls.
- [ ] Graceful shutdown: SIGTERM closes the socket, drains in-flight requests, closes the DB cleanly.
- [ ] Integration test: kill the daemon mid-request, adapter receives a clear error, next adapter call auto-spawns a fresh daemon and succeeds.
- [ ] `angreal ci` passes.

## Dependencies

- PROJEC-T-0064 (MuninnEngine trait)
- PROJEC-T-0065 (engine implements the trait)

## Implementation Notes

- This is the design's heaviest architectural addition. Keep the IPC protocol boring — JSON over Unix socket — and resist any premature optimization (binary framing, shared memory, etc.).
- The repo-hash in the socket path lets multiple muninn instances coexist (different repos, different daemons).
- For tests, allow overriding the socket path via env var so each test gets its own daemon.

